<subSubSection id="C3246572FFA8C907FF62FE19FD6BFE12" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FFA8C907FF62FE19FD6BFE12" blockId="9.[151,1437,258,1294]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFA8C907FF62FE19FEC0FE6E" bold="true" box="[199,334,403,429]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the Kaiabi indigenous people, whose former territory included the distribution areas of this species; noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FFA8C907FF62FE51FE05FCD6" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FFA8C907FF62FE51FE05FCD6" blockId="9.[151,1437,258,1294]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFA8C907FF62FE51FECCFE36" bold="true" box="[199,322,475,501]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
