</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFA8C907FC72FE51FBD8FE35" box="[983,1110,475,502]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–50" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[188,1399,196,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-17@17.[173,1414,181,1843]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 45–50. Sadala punicea Simon 45–47 Male (IBSP 9361), left palp (45 prolateral, 46 ventral, 47 retrolateral); 28–50. Female (IBSP 7362) (48 epigyne, 49 vulva, 50 schematic course of internal duct system). C—conductor; E—embolus; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MAB—muscle attachment bands; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SP—spermathecae; st—second turn of duct system; ST—subtegulum; TP—triangular projection. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550229" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550229/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs 45–47</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFFA8C907FB37FE51FAABFE36" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[1170,1317,475,501]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Sadala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yuyapichis" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFA8C907FB37FE51FAABFE36" box="[1170,1317,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">S. yuyapichis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFA8C907FA8EFE51FA12FE36" bold="true" box="[1323,1436,475,501]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FFA8C907FA8EFE51FA12FE36" box="[1323,1436,475,501]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFA8C907FF3AFE75FE91FDD9" box="[159,287,511,538]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–85" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1758,1782]" captionTargetBox="[164,1419,463,1720]" captionTargetId="figure-136@25.[153,1434,453,1734]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 83–85. Sadala yuyapichis spec. nov., male (MUSM, holotype), left palp (83 prolateral, 84 ventral 85 retrolateral). Scale lines: 1 mm. C—conductor; E–embolus; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550251" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550251/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs 83–85</figureCitation>
) by the palp with embolus arising from tegulum at 4 o’clock position (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFA8C907FB93FE75FB04FDDA" box="[1078,1162,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–18" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox="[171,1406,196,1772]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[159,1428,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 13–18. Sadala kaiabi spec. nov. 13–15 Male (IBSP 246434, holotype), left palp (13 prolateral, 14 ventral, 15 retrolateral); 16–18 Female (IBSP 233316, paratype) (16 epigyne, 17 vulva, 18 schematic course of internal ducts system). C—conductor; CO—copulatory opening; E—embolus; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; TP— triangular projection; PTA—prolateral tibial projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SP—spermathecae; st—second turn of duct system; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550209" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550209/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). They are distinguished from both species by the RTA tapering and pointed (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFA8C907FD7DFDA9FCA7FDFD" box="[728,809,547,574]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–18" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox="[171,1406,196,1772]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[159,1428,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 13–18. Sadala kaiabi spec. nov. 13–15 Male (IBSP 246434, holotype), left palp (13 prolateral, 14 ventral, 15 retrolateral); 16–18 Female (IBSP 233316, paratype) (16 epigyne, 17 vulva, 18 schematic course of internal ducts system). C—conductor; CO—copulatory opening; E—embolus; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; TP— triangular projection; PTA—prolateral tibial projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SP—spermathecae; st—second turn of duct system; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550209" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550209/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
) and conductor tip barely surpassing the anterior margin of the alveolus (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFA8C907FEEFFDCDFE12FDA2" box="[330,412,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–18" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox="[171,1406,196,1772]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[159,1428,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 13–18. Sadala kaiabi spec. nov. 13–15 Male (IBSP 246434, holotype), left palp (13 prolateral, 14 ventral, 15 retrolateral); 16–18 Female (IBSP 233316, paratype) (16 epigyne, 17 vulva, 18 schematic course of internal ducts system). C—conductor; CO—copulatory opening; E—embolus; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; TP— triangular projection; PTA—prolateral tibial projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SP—spermathecae; st—second turn of duct system; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550209" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550209/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
) (RTA roughly the same width throughout, not pointed and conductor tip surpassing the anterior margin of the alveolus by at least half its length in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFFA8C907FCAFFDE1FCF0FD46" authorityName="Simon IBSP" authorityYear="1880" box="[778,894,619,645]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Sadala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punicea">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFA8C907FCAFFDE1FCF0FD46" box="[778,894,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">S. punicea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFFA8C907FC17FDE1FBC8FD46" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[946,1094,619,645]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Sadala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yuyapichis" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFA8C907FC17FDE1FBC8FD46" box="[946,1094,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">S. yuyapichis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFA8C907FBEEFDE1FB33FD46" bold="true" box="[1099,1213,619,645]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FFA8C907FBEEFDE1FB33FD46" box="[1099,1213,619,645]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
). Females resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFFA8C907FF53FD05FE03FD6A" authorityName=": Simon" authorityYear="1880" box="[246,397,655,681]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Sadala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="keyserlingi">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFA8C907FF53FD05FE03FD6A" box="[246,397,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">S. keyserlingi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFA8C907FE3FFD05FD94FD6A" box="[410,538,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–29" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1793,1817]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,195,1758]" captionTargetId="figure-23@12.[154,1434,181,1769]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 24–29. Sadala keyserlingi Simon 24–26 Male (INPA 4563), left palp (24 prolateral, 25 ventral, 26 retrolateral); 27–29 Female (MNHN 2459, syntype) (27 epigyne, 28 vulva, 29 schematic course of internal duct system). C—conductor; DpP—dorsal proximal projection; E—embolus; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; TP—triangular projection; PTA—prolateral tibial projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SP—spermathecae; st—second turn of duct system; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550215/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs 27–29</figureCitation>
) by the epigyne with MS triangular, wider than long, widest anteriorly (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFA8C907FA9DFD05FA01FD69" box="[1336,1423,655,682]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–18" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox="[171,1406,196,1772]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[159,1428,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 13–18. Sadala kaiabi spec. nov. 13–15 Male (IBSP 246434, holotype), left palp (13 prolateral, 14 ventral, 15 retrolateral); 16–18 Female (IBSP 233316, paratype) (16 epigyne, 17 vulva, 18 schematic course of internal ducts system). C—conductor; CO—copulatory opening; E—embolus; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; TP— triangular projection; PTA—prolateral tibial projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SP—spermathecae; st—second turn of duct system; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550209" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550209/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs 16</figureCitation>
). They are distinguished from the those of the latter species by the vulva with FW slender, slightly wider than the ducts between first and second turns (FW dilated, four times wider than ducts between first and second turns in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFFA8C907FA22FD5DFE9CFCD6" authorityName=": Simon" authorityYear="1880" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Sadala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="keyserlingi">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFA8C907FA22FD5DFE9CFCD6" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">S. keyserlingi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFA8C907FE8EFD71FEF0FCD6" box="[299,382,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–18" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox="[171,1406,196,1772]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[159,1428,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 13–18. Sadala kaiabi spec. nov. 13–15 Male (IBSP 246434, holotype), left palp (13 prolateral, 14 ventral, 15 retrolateral); 16–18 Female (IBSP 233316, paratype) (16 epigyne, 17 vulva, 18 schematic course of internal ducts system). C—conductor; CO—copulatory opening; E—embolus; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; TP— triangular projection; PTA—prolateral tibial projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SP—spermathecae; st—second turn of duct system; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550209" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550209/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FFA8C907FF62FC95FAAAFB2A" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FFA8C907FF62FC95FA0CFC2E" blockId="9.[151,1437,258,1294]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFA8C907FF62FC95FDA4FCFA" bold="true" box="[199,554,799,825]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Description. Male (
<typeStatus id="5485885BFFA8C907FE0AFC95FD93FCFA" box="[431,541,799,825]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">holotype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
Total length 10.3. Prosoma: 5.0 long, 5.1 wide. Opisthosoma: 5.0. Long, 3.0 wide. Eyes: diameters: 0.40, 0.34, 0.25, 0.30; interdistances: 0.35, 0.22, 0.55, 0.55, 0.37, 0.25. Legs: I: 29.7 (8.0, 3.0, 8.1, 8.5, 2.1); II: 31.6 (8.5, 3.1, 8.7, 9.0, 2.3); III: 21.8 (6.5, 2.5, 5.5, 5.7, 1.6); IV: 24.3 (7.1, 2.4, 6.2, 6.7, 1.9). Spination follows the generic pattern, except tibia II: d1-0-1 and patella III: p0. Palp: RTA two times longer than wide, disto-ventrad in retrolateral view; PTA triangular, as wide as long; subtegulum not visible in ventral view; tegulum rounded; conductor 1.5 times longer than wide; roughly the same with throughout (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFA8C907FB3BFC59FAAEFC2D" box="[1182,1312,979,1006]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–18" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox="[171,1406,196,1772]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[159,1428,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 13–18. Sadala kaiabi spec. nov. 13–15 Male (IBSP 246434, holotype), left palp (13 prolateral, 14 ventral, 15 retrolateral); 16–18 Female (IBSP 233316, paratype) (16 epigyne, 17 vulva, 18 schematic course of internal ducts system). C—conductor; CO—copulatory opening; E—embolus; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; TP— triangular projection; PTA—prolateral tibial projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SP—spermathecae; st—second turn of duct system; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550209" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550209/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs 13–15</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFA8C907FA8EFC59FAFBFC2E" box="[1323,1397,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–23" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1042,1066]" captionTargetBox="[166,1413,199,1009]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[164,1423,181,1018]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 19–23. Sadala kaiabi spec. nov. 19–21 Male (IBSP 246434, holotype), left palp (19 prolateral, 20 ventral, 21 retrolateral); 22–23 Female (IBSP 233316, paratype) (22 epigyne, 23 vulva). Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550213" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550213/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">19–21</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FFA8C907FF62FC7DFACBFB06" blockId="9.[151,1437,258,1294]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFA8C907FF62FC7DFDDCFBD2" bold="true" box="[199,594,1015,1041]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Female (IBSP 233316, 
<typeStatus id="5485885BFFA8C907FE71FC7DFDCBFBD2" box="[468,581,1015,1041]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">paratype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
Total length 17.8. Prosoma 6.8 long, 6.3 wide. Opisthosoma 10.8 long, 7.0 wide. Eyes: diameters: 0.55, 0.46, 0.34, 0.42; interdistances: 0.43, 0.25, 0.70, 0.70, 0.40, 0.28. Legs: I: 29.0 (8.2, 3.1, 7.6, 8.0, 2.1); II: 30.8 (8.8, 3.4, 8.1, 8.4, 2.1); III: 22.6 (6.8, 2.7, 5.8, 5.5, 1.8); IV: 25.1 (7.4, 2.7, 6.3, 6.7, 2.0). Spination follows the generic pattern. Epigyne: EF wider than long; MAB embedded in EF (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFA8C907FB0DFBE9FB73FBBE" box="[1192,1277,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–23" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1042,1066]" captionTargetBox="[166,1413,199,1009]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[164,1423,181,1018]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 19–23. Sadala kaiabi spec. nov. 19–21 Male (IBSP 246434, holotype), left palp (19 prolateral, 20 ventral, 21 retrolateral); 22–23 Female (IBSP 233316, paratype) (22 epigyne, 23 vulva). Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550213" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550213/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
); LL touching each other posteriorly; TP roughly two times wider than long (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFA8C907FCF7FB0DFC26FB62" box="[850,936,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–18" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox="[171,1406,196,1772]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[159,1428,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 13–18. Sadala kaiabi spec. nov. 13–15 Male (IBSP 246434, holotype), left palp (13 prolateral, 14 ventral, 15 retrolateral); 16–18 Female (IBSP 233316, paratype) (16 epigyne, 17 vulva, 18 schematic course of internal ducts system). C—conductor; CO—copulatory opening; E—embolus; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; TP— triangular projection; PTA—prolateral tibial projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SP—spermathecae; st—second turn of duct system; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550209" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550209/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs 16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFA8C907FC11FB0DFC5AFB62" box="[948,980,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–23" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1042,1066]" captionTargetBox="[166,1413,199,1009]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[164,1423,181,1018]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 19–23. Sadala kaiabi spec. nov. 19–21 Male (IBSP 246434, holotype), left palp (19 prolateral, 20 ventral, 21 retrolateral); 22–23 Female (IBSP 233316, paratype) (22 epigyne, 23 vulva). Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550213" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550213/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">22</figureCitation>
). Vulva: internal ducts with FW posteromediad; GP short, rounded, emerging from ducts at second turn; SP spherical; FD laterad (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFA8C907FB29FB21FA80FB06" box="[1164,1294,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–18" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox="[171,1406,196,1772]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[159,1428,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 13–18. Sadala kaiabi spec. nov. 13–15 Male (IBSP 246434, holotype), left palp (13 prolateral, 14 ventral, 15 retrolateral); 16–18 Female (IBSP 233316, paratype) (16 epigyne, 17 vulva, 18 schematic course of internal ducts system). C—conductor; CO—copulatory opening; E—embolus; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; TP— triangular projection; PTA—prolateral tibial projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SP—spermathecae; st—second turn of duct system; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550209" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550209/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs 17–18</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFA8C907FABCFB21FAB7FB06" box="[1305,1337,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–23" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1042,1066]" captionTargetBox="[166,1413,199,1009]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[164,1423,181,1018]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 19–23. Sadala kaiabi spec. nov. 19–21 Male (IBSP 246434, holotype), left palp (19 prolateral, 20 ventral, 21 retrolateral); 22–23 Female (IBSP 233316, paratype) (22 epigyne, 23 vulva). Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550213" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550213/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">23</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FFA8C907FF62FB45FAAAFB2A" blockId="9.[151,1437,258,1294]" box="[199,1316,1231,1258]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFA8C907FF62FB45FEB1FB2A" bold="true" box="[199,319,1231,1257]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Variation.</emphasis>
Females (n = 2): total length 15.4–17.8; prosoma length 6.8–7.2; femur I length 8.2–8.6.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FFA8C907FF62FB79FB9FFACE" box="[199,1041,1267,1294]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FFA8C907FF62FB79FB9FFACE" blockId="9.[151,1437,258,1294]" box="[199,1041,1267,1294]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFA8C907FF62FB79FEEFFACE" bold="true" box="[199,353,1267,1293]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known from northern state of 
<collectingRegion id="49FAF81BFFA8C907FD18FB7EFCDFFACE" box="[701,849,1267,1294]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3297669FFA8C907FCF9FB79FC2EFACE" box="[860,928,1267,1293]" name="Brazil" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFA8C907FC15FB79FB8AFACE" box="[944,1028,1267,1293]" captionStart="FIGURES 89–90" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,181,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-17@27.[155,1432,181,1916]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 89–90. Distribution maps for Sadala spp. 89 S. tabatinga spec. nov., S. velox Simon, S. nanay spec. nov., S. punicea Simon 90 S. rufa (Keyserling), S. kaiabi spec. nov., S. keyserlingi Simon, S. nigristernis Simon, S. yuyapichis spec. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550257/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 90</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
